# Phase 3 — Generate Semantic Layers

For each timestamp:

```text
T1 image
↓
Vegetation model
↓
Vegetation mask

T1 image
↓
Building model
↓
Building mask

T1 image
↓
Road model
↓
Road mask

T1 image
↓
Water model
↓
Water mask
```

Same for:

```text
T2
```

Result:

```text
T1 semantic map
T2 semantic map
```

***

# Phase 4 — Image Registration

Align:

```text
T1
T2
```

using:

```text
SIFT
+
FLANN
+
RANSAC
```

to remove geometric shifts.

Pipeline:

```text
Keypoints
↓
Matches
↓
Homography
↓
Warp
↓
Aligned images
```

✅ Essential for change detection

***

# Phase 5 — Semantic Change Detection

Instead of:

```text
Pixel difference
```

you compare:

```text
Vegetation(T1) vs Vegetation(T2)
Building(T1)   vs Building(T2)
Road(T1)       vs Road(T2)
Water(T1)      vs Water(T2)
```

Examples:

```text
Vegetation → Building
```

means:

```text
Urban expansion
```

***

```text
Building → Empty
```

means:

```text
Demolition
```

***

```text
Vegetation → Vegetation
```

means:

```text
No change
```

***

# Phase 6 — SemDINO-Style Model

Final architecture:

```text
T1
↓
DINOv3

T2
↓
DINOv3

Semantic masks
↓
Fusion

Feature difference
↓
Transformer Decoder
↓
Change Map
```

Outputs:

```text
No Change
Vegetation Loss
New Building
Road Construction
Water Change
```

